Original review 2015: It's a shame that hands are not really random and that AI don't realistically react to the different risks in the hands they are playing. They have play money and they don't care about losing so they behave differently to how someone with something to lose would play. Poker is about skill and luck but this game unfortunately is more about luck than skill. Fun for a while but due to in app purchase changes the main pc game, I feel there is some slewing of results.  Updated 2017: after returning and playing for another week, my review above stands. Only way to win is through strategies that would only work on a computer player. Boring. If I bet and play how I would with real players, I would win at least twice as much as I do in this simplistic poker simulation. Good for learning poker, nothing more.

BEWARE OF GAME DESIGN - IT'S A SCAM TO EMPTY YOUR WALLET. READ THIS REVIEW FIRST BEFORE YOU BUY. The major issue with this game is that it is designed to FORCE you into in-app purchases even though you paid for the full version. If you're low on cash you get thrown into a loop where you can't advance the day without playing a game of poker which you can't afford to play because you're low on cash! You have no choice but to lose all your achievements and restart from the  beginning or make in-app purchases! If you travel, the days pass but you don't collect rent during that time ensuring that you don't earn cash in other ways. You can watch ads for few extra game dollars but only for limited number of times.  The AI is good but it purposely lacks the ability to tweak it so you end up playing tough games right off the bat. This focus on milking you for all you're worth takes the fun out of the game and ensures that your losing streaks become guaranteed in-app purchases. One would think that by paying for the full version you'd should be able to play the game without in-app purchases.
